farenheit question on the third section in his escape down river montag has a revelation about burning and the sun what epiphany does he experience what does this mean in relationship to books and ideas here's ideas on the first question montag considers the moon which in turn reminds him of the sun and then of fire he concludes that the sun actually burns time scorching away the years and all the people on the planet this is a puzzling statement but it means simply that time represented by the rising and setting of the sun will inevitably destroy people and everything they have worked for he realizes that if he continues to burn things as he has all his life everything worthwhile will be destroyed even more quickly he begins to think of his life as having a different purpose of using his life to preserve rather than destroy soon after he has these thoughts he sees the flame that the hobos warm their hands over for the first time in his life he discovers that fire can sustain life as well as destroy it no ideas for the second Fahrenheit 451 Kain (Legacy of Kain) Philosophiae Naturalis Principia Mathematica Futurama (TV series - season 5) Goodness and value theory Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Meaning of life Richard Allen (reverend) Causality Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Darth Vader Four Quartets Philosophy of language Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Futurama (TV series - season 4) Atomism Solar system K' The Structure of Scientific Revolutions A Course In Miracles Out of the Silent Planet Simone Weil Soul Identity and change Extraterrestrial life Mid-Autumn Festival Definition of planet Sudoku Bad Wolf Rei Ayanami Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Reality Angel Transformers: Cybertron Jiddu Krishnamurti Heliocentrism Wealth Pluto Ages of Myst Chronology of Jesus StarCraft: Revelations Micronauts Nicomachean Ethics Blood (computer game) Christian eschatology Past teachings of Prem Rawat Sense and reference Predestination Jacob Neus